# .lycheeignore
#
# Regex patterns (one per line) for URLs that lychee should skip.
#
# Rules:
#   1. Add an entry ONLY when a link is verified-good in a browser but
#      consistently fails in CI (e.g. hosts that 999 on HEAD requests,
#      hosts that block GitHub-Actions egress, or rate-limit aggressively).
#   2. Every entry MUST be preceded by a one-line comment explaining
#      WHY it is ignored (host behaviour + date noticed).
#   3. Prefer narrow patterns (specific host) over broad ones.
#   4. Re-evaluate entries during Phase 7.5 review passes.
#
# Examples (commented out, kept for reference):
# # linkedin.com — returns HTTP 999 on HEAD requests from CI runners (2026-04)
# ^https?://(www\.)?linkedin\.com/
# # twitter.com / x.com — aggressive bot-detection breaks unauthenticated checks (2026-04)
# ^https?://(www\.)?(twitter|x)\.com/
